The Chief of Army Staff, Lieutenant General Yusuf Buratai, weekend said the Nigerian Army was working to sustain the unity of Nigeria. Buratai spoke at the Nigeria Military School as Reviewing Officer of the 60th Passing Out Parade (POP) of the school. Represented by the Commandant, Depot, Nigerian Army, Major-General Victor Okwudili Ezugwu, Buratain said: “We will also continue to support the civil authorities in ensuring that citizens of the country are safe and protected in the course of pursuing their legitimate activities. “The security of thecountry is of great concern to the Federal Government and indeed all Nigerians.”